Controversial Nollywood actor, Uche Maduagwu, has slammed actor, Yul Edochie, after he announced welcoming a son with actress, Judy Moghalu, whom he described as his second wife. Maduagwu, in a post shared on his Instagram page on Wednesday, said it is an abomination for a Christian to marry two wives. He said he knew something was spiritually wrong with Yul when he danced ‘Zazu’, insisting that he must build his house before talking of the presidency. According to him, Yul is the son of veteran actor, Pete Edochie, who is said to be a Knight in the Catholic Church. Reacting, Uche wrote: “It is an abomination for a Christian to marry two wives. I knew something was spiritually wrong when you danced Zazu on naira for church. “Build your home before you talk of the presidency.” Recall that Yul on Wednesday shocked fans after announcing his son‘s existence by his second wife, Judy Austin Muoghalu. He wrote on social media: “It’s time for the world to meet my son. His name is STAR DIKE MUNACHIMSO YUL-EDOCHIE. “Born by my second wife @judyaustin1 And I love him so much, just as much as I love my other children.” The senior wife of Edochie, who has five children for him, took to the comment section writing: “May God judge you both.” —